{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe design has sharp edges (hot-path cost, concurrency on the shared branch, rate-limit,\nno_mutate, absent marker). Only tests lock the invariants so future ensures can be added\nsafely.\n\n## What\nAdd behavioral tests covering: git-level idempotency (`run_ensures` twice on a converged store\n→ zero new commits); hot-path regression (a common mutation never invokes `run_ensures`, spawns\nno ENSURE-UNIT git-config subprocess — gc.auto/gc.autoDetach/merge.ours; the write path's own\n`git config user.name` author lookup in `_seam.author()` is expected and excluded — and reads\n`.ensure-applied` at most once per process); concurrency (two processes running the\nsweep on the same checkout serialize under the write lock and converge; `.ensure-applied`\nwritten atomically, no torn/lost state); no_mutate (library read-only fsck mutates nothing);\nabsent/garbage `.ensure-applied` (→ empty set → converges, no re-commit storm). The fsck byte-parity/help-golden tests are owned by WS3, and the pending-hint unit tests by WS2 — NOT here.\n\n## Scope\nIn: the behavioral test suite for WS1-2 invariants.\nOut: fsck byte-parity/help goldens (WS3), the feature code itself (WS1-3), docs (WS4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Idempotency test: `run_ensures()` twice on a converged store makes zero new commits/pushes (git-log assertion)\n- [ ] Hot-path regression test: a ticket mutation never calls `run_ensures`, spawns no ENSURE-UNIT git-config subprocess (gc.auto/gc.autoDetach/merge.ours — the mutation's own `git config user.name` author lookup via `_seam.author()` is expected and explicitly excluded from the assertion), and reads `.ensure-applied` at most once per process\n- [ ] Concurrency test: two real OS processes sweeping the same checkout serialize under the store write lock (`_store/lock.py`) and converge; `.ensure-applied` is written atomically (no torn/lost writes)\n- [ ] no_mutate test: a library read-only fsck surface (no_mutate=True) mutates nothing and never runs the sweep\n- [ ] absent/garbage-marker test: a missing or garbage `.ensure-applied` degrades to empty-set (pending=all) without crashing"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783644804566972001,"uuid":"20f1614e-f76b-460e-b2c4-d5531b192da9"}